AI System to Detect Manipulated Bank Statements Using Image Forensics & Machine Learning


---

1Ô∏è‚É£ Problem Statement (Short & Clear)

Banks receive thousands of bank statements and financial documents during loan processing.
Many applicants edit PDFs/images using Photoshop/Canva to fake salary, account balance, or transactions.
Manual verification cannot detect subtle manipulations.

We need an AI-based system that automatically analyzes a bank statement and detects whether it has been edited or tampered using image forensics + ML.


---

2Ô∏è‚É£ Solution Overview (What our system will do)

Our solution is an end-to-end AI pipeline that:

‚úî Converts PDFs to images

‚úî Extracts text using OCR

‚úî Applies Image Forensics techniques:

Error Level Analysis (ELA)

Noise pattern analysis

Compression difference

Metadata & timestamp check

Font & alignment consistency check


‚úî ML Model

Trains a classifier to detect whether a document is genuine or manipulated.

‚úî Final Output

Tampering Score (0‚Äì100)

Highlighted suspicious areas

Reasons (font mismatch, ELA anomaly, compression difference)

OCR text summary (optional)


This will act as a fraud detection layer for banks/fintech companies.


